parameters: I went for a maze idea. But I want to make each path needed for traversing
the dungeon in full. Youll have to go down the lower right path first to open
the way to the next, so on and so forth. That way its not really a maze and more
just a large dungeon. I want to make each path more worthwhile than that as well,
treasures and the like. That way players arent angry about needing to go down
each path. I want it to stay interesting so we can do traps, alter paths a
little bit (ie needing to do a small puzzle to get through an area yaddayadda)
I also already have an idea for the lighting. I want it to not all be lit when
you get in. I want Miana to have to do something for the first paths lights to
come on. Then later on each subsequent path will be lit in turn. This will keep
players going in the right direction and keep the scale of the map out of the
players eyes as they walk around. Keeping is special and not overwhelming.
I also dont want any light to be overlapping walls really. so using the 1,2,3,4
directional lighting to keep things within walls. Once again, to not show any
paths other than the paths they are on. Also it just makes sense to not have
